                    "created": "2006-12-01T18:52:01.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-12-01T18:52:01.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/12743",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=indygreg",
                        "name": "indygreg",
                        "displayName": "Gregory Szorc",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "You are getting the error because you have not registered a default logger.  When you called registerLogger() with a second argument, 'File' in your case, you told the log handler to register your log under the name 'File.'  Had you omitted this argument, the file adapter would be registered as the default logger.\n\nTo correct the issue, you need to either omit the second argument to registerLogger() or make a call to Zend_Log::setDefaultLogger('File')\n\nPersonally, I don't think that this is a bug.  It is the way the component is designed.  If you really want to name your logger, just make the extra call to setDefaultLogger().\n\nCorrect code is as follows:\n\n{code}\nZend_Log::registerLogger(new Zend_Log_Adapter_File('data\/logs\/ecmc.log'),'File');\nZend_Log::setDefaultLogger('FIle');\nZend_Log::log('First logging message');\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=indygreg",
                        "name": "indygreg",
                        "displayName": "Gregory Szorc",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-02-15T00:46:47.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-02-15T00:46:47.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/13546",
                    "author": {
